== Potato Wedges ==

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Cut @potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch-thick wedges. Toss on a #baking sheet{} with a
large drizzle of @cooking oil{2%tsp}, half the @fry seasoning{1%tbsp}, @salt{}, and
@pepper{}.

Roast on top rack until browned and tender, ~{20-25%minutes}.

== Chickpea Salad ==

While potatoes roast, drain and rinse @chickpeas{1}; pat dry with #paper towels{}.

Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2} greens (save whites for another use).

Finely chop @parsley{1/4%ounce}. Quarter @lemon{1}.

Thinly slice @tomato{1} into rounds; season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Place chickpeas in a #medium bowl{} and mash with a #potato masher{} or fork until
about half the chickpeas are smooth (leave some larger pieces for texture!).

Add scallion greens, parsley, @guacamole{1/2%cup}, @garlic powder{1%tsp}, a large
drizzle of @olive oil{9%tsp}, and as much lemon juice as you like. Season generously
with @salt{1%tsp} (we used 2 tsp for 4 servings) and pepper. Stir until combined.

> Bacon is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.

== Toasted Sourdough & Bacon ==

Brush each side of @sourdough bread{4%slices} with a drizzle of olive oil.

Heat a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add bread; toast until golden brown,
~{2-3%minutes} per side (work in batches for 4 servings, adding more olive oil
between batches as needed).

Turn off heat; wipe out pan used for bread. Return pan to medium-high heat. Add
@bacon{4%ounce}; cook, turning occasionally and adjusting heat if browning too
quickly, until crispy, ~{6-10%minutes}. Transfer to a #paper-towel-lined plate{}.

== Assembly ==

Top half the toasted sourdough with chickpea salad and seasoned tomato.

Close sandwiches and halve on a diagonal.

Add bacon to sandwiches.

Divide sandwiches and potato wedges between plates. Serve.